dmaze_data.description: To officially start "Project Phoenix", a new digital marketing campaign aimed at increasing brand awareness by 20% in the 25-40 age segment. The meeting's goal was to define key messages, assign responsibilities, and set a six-week timeline.
dmaze_data.title: Project Phoenix Kickoff Meeting

dmaze_data.description: Lise Berg and Jonas Fredriksen will collaborate to create detailed storyboards for the video concepts.
dmaze_data.title: Develop storyboard for 5 campaign videos

dmaze_data.conclusion: The main message will be "Simplicity in everyday life". The campaign will focus primarily on Instagram (Reels) and TikTok. A series of 5 short videos will be produced.
dmaze_data.description: The team conducted a workshop to finalize the main message. The discussion settled on three core concepts: "Simplicity in everyday life", "Sustainable choice", and "Modern design". Jonas presented data indicating that the target audience responds best to visual content on Instagram and TikTok. Lise Berg proposed producing a series of short video clips showing the product in real situations.
dmaze_data.title: Definition of Core Message and Target Audience

dmaze_data.description: Silje Dahl will send a formal request to management to approve the increased budget of 100,000 NOK.
dmaze_data.title: Get approval for revised budget

dmaze_data.conclusion: The budget is increased to 600,000 NOK. Silje Dahl will take responsibility for obtaining formal approval. The launch date is confirmed.
dmaze_data.description: Silje Dahl presented a preliminary budget of 500,000 NOK for production, advertising, and agency fees. Erik Larsen suggested increasing the ad budget by 100,000 NOK for sufficient reach on TikTok, which could be taken from the travel budget with less usage. The timeline was set with a launch in week 3, 2026.
dmaze_data.title: Budget and Timeline
